{
  "stem": "19690.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So it was a very watery grave, and it's something that I don't think I'll ever forget.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "This total insanity of people living like animals and being treated like animals and not being able to do anything about it, the total lack of power to do anything about not only your own, but your fellow man's condition, was unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Around Christmas, my aunt who had her mother in Italy at the time found out that their mother had moved to Oleron.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "She was one of these free spirits.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "She had been a widow for many, many years and she just traveled wherever she wanted to, or she could.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And she had relocated to Oleron and we got passes for my aunt, my cousin, and me, to go to Oleron for a day to visit with her.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "This was the first day in civilization that I had seen since October 22nd.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was very heavily guarded.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were double barbed wire all around the camp and guard towers all over.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was not a place where you could easily walk away from.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And being in a foreign country, besides, with no one to go to, it would have been extremely difficult to find any way of escaping.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The OSE came into play at that point, which was Oeuvre de Secours aux Enfants, a children's organization which was financed from America.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they started coming to see us, help us with extra clothing warmer blankets, things like that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And-- but to escape would at this time had been not thinkable.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was very difficult for my aunt and my cousin and me to come back to camp that night, but we did.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
